  "display_title": "Smiling Friends",
  "html_content": "<div class=\"mw-body-content mw-content-ltr\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin:0.5em auto; max-width:50em;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"border:none; color:#B2B7F2; font-family:'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size:3em; font-weight:bold; line-height:41px; padding:0 16px 0 0; vertical-align:top; width:20px;\">“\n</td>\n<td style=\"border:none; font-size:1.2em; font-style:italic; padding:0; vertical-align:middle;\">And don’t forget about me, Grease! I could have done it. [...] I mean, no, but I totally could have.\n</td>\n<td style=\"border:none; color:#B2B7F2; font-family:'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size:3em; font-weight:bold; line-height:11px; padding:0 0 0 16px; vertical-align:bottom; width:20px\">”\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"font-size:smaller; padding:8px 36px; text-align:right;\"><cite>Lines by Grease, which Chris was to have voiced</cite>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"/cwcki/File:Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"thumbimage\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"88\" src=\"/w/images/thumb/6/6f/Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png/300px-Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png\" srcset=\"/w/images/thumb/6/6f/Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png/450px-Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/6f/Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png/600px-Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png 2x\" width=\"300\"/></a> <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a class=\"internal\" href=\"/cwcki/File:Smiling_Friends_-_Grease.png\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Grease</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Smiling Friends</b></i> is an animated series airing on <a href=\"/cwcki/Adult_Swim\" title=\"Adult Swim\">Adult Swim</a>. It premiered in <a href=\"/cwcki/April_2020\" title=\"April 2020\">April 2020</a> and ran for three seasons. \n</p><p>Zach Hadel, co-creator of the series and voice of the co-lead character Charlie, stated in an interview with <i><a href=\"/cwcki/The_Create_Unknown\" title=\"The Create Unknown\">The Create Unknown</a></i> podcast<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-cu_1-0\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cu-1\">[1]</a></sup> that Chris was very nearly going to have a small voice role on the show. However, that plan ultimately fell through, due to a number of concerns; they had already used up their budget for cameo roles, and were told they would have to cast Chris in more roles if he got the part. Plus, the network was seemingly aware of Chris's <a href=\"/cwcki/Honest_Content\" title=\"Honest Content\">inability to keep a secret</a>, and were concerned that he would potentially blab about his role before it aired (which would be problematic, as <i>Smiling Friends</i> is known for its surprise cameos). It's worth noting these negotiations happened before the <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/cwcki/Affair_With_Mother\" title=\"Affair With Mother\">incest scandal</a> broke out.\n</p><p>In the season 3 premiere, there was a reference to <a href=\"/cwcki/Bob_Chandler\" title=\"Bob Chandler\">Bob Chandler</a>'s line in <a href=\"/cwcki/THAT_IS_MY_HOUSE\" title=\"THAT IS MY HOUSE\">THAT IS MY HOUSE</a>. Almost a month later, Chris responded by lightly critiquing the show, saying it relied too much on <a href=\"/cwcki/Random-access_humor\" title=\"Random-access humor\">random-access humor</a> and the dialog was too fast.<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-2\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Proposed_role\">Proposed role</span></h2>\n<p>Chris was going to have three lines as a talking grease puddle in the episode \"Who Violently Murdered Simon S. Salty?\", which was the fifth episode of the series. The plot revolved around characters attempting to solve a murder. At one point a grease puddle says, \"And don’t forget about me, Grease! I could have done it.\" Charlie answers, \"Um... alright, well, did you do it?\" And Grease answers, \"I mean, no, but I totally could have.\" Later on, as Charlie and Pim rewind the surveillance tape to uncover the murderer, the grease puddle prompts the two to continue one last time, revealing the victim actually died of a heart attack.\n</p><p>The episode aired on 16 <a href=\"/cwcki/January_2022\" title=\"January 2022\">January 2022</a>, with the grease puddle being voiced by fellow animator and Chris follower Harry Partridge doing a rough impression of Chris.\n</p><p>Zach Hadel mentioned having been inspired by both Chris's segment in <i><a href=\"/cwcki/Shrek_Retold\" title=\"Shrek Retold\">Shrek Retold</a></i> and the full version of <a href=\"/cwcki/THAT_IS_MY_HOUSE\" title=\"THAT IS MY HOUSE\">THAT IS MY HOUSE</a> when coming up with the role.<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-cu_1-1\"><a href=\"#cite_note-cu-1\">[1]</a></sup>\n</p><p>Chris is aware that he nearly had the role. In the February 2024 livestream <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/cwcki/Round_2_-_Media_Share_Suggestion_Live_Stream\" title=\"Round 2 - Media Share Suggestion Live Stream\">Round 2 - Media Share Suggestion Live Stream</a>, Chris is asked by a fan about his thoughts on <i>Smiling Friends</i>, and Chris responded that it's a decent show, then performed the two Grease lines.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-cu-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-cu_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-cu_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=06R7mspyoRw\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=06R7mspyoRw</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/cwcki/November_2025_social_media_posts#Referenced_on_Smiling_Friends\" title=\"November 2025 social media posts\">November 2025 social media posts#Referenced on Smiling Friends</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\";\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding:2px;\">\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse\" style=\"width:100%;background:transparent;color:inherit;;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\" style=\";\"><div style=\"float:left; width:6em;text-align:left;\"> <span class=\"noprint plainlinksneverexpand\" style=\"white-space:nowrap; font-weight:normal; font-size:xx-small; ;;border:none;;\"><a href=\"/cwcki/Template:TV\" title=\"Template:TV\"><span style=\";;border:none;;\" title=\"View this template\">v</span></a> <span style=\"font-size:80%;\">•</span> <a class=\"new\" href=\"/w/index.php?title=Template_talk:TV&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" title=\"Template talk:TV (page does not exist)\"><span style=\"color:#002bb8;;;border:none;;\" title=\"Discussion about this template\">d</span></a> <span style=\"font-size:80%;\">•</span> <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//sonichu.com/w/index.php?title=Template:TV&amp;action=edit\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"color:#002bb8;;;border:none;;\" title=\"You can edit this template. Please use the preview button before saving.\">e</span></a> </span>  </div> <span style=\"font-size:110%;\"> <a href=\"/cwcki/Chris_and_television\" title=\"Chris and television\">Television</a> and <a href=\"/cwcki/Chris_and_video_games\" title=\"Chris and video games\">video games</a></span>\n</th></tr>\n<tr style=\"height:2px;\">\n<td>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"navbox-group\" style=\";;\"><a href=\"/cwcki/Anime\" title=\"Anime\">Anime</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"navbox-list navbox-odd\" style=\"text-align:left;border-left:2px solid #fdfdfd; width:100%;padding:0px;;;\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<i> <a href=\"/cwcki/Dragon_Ball\" title=\"Dragon Ball\">Dragon Ball